               <head>Rawzat al-va'izin</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Rawz̤at al-vāʻiẓīn by Muʻīn al-Dīn
									Farāhī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85067900" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Or_15582-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658505.0x000001 viaf_51672236">Muʻīn al-Dīn
									Farāhī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658505.0x000001 viaf_51672236" type="supplied">معين الدين فراهي</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22055">Rawz̤at al-vāʻiẓīn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_22055">روضة الواعظین</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>A compilation of religious and ethical teachings, maxims and
									stories, planned in the form of a copious and wide-ranging
									commentary upon forty Hadith by Mu‘īn al-Dīn Farāhī called
									Miskīn (d. 907/1501-2). </p>
                        <p>Other contents: f. 1r, 2r, 3r and 4r, ownership inscriptions; 3r,
									a Qur’ānic phrase used as a prayer; 4r, verses and attributions;
									f. 4r-5r, 327r, obscured seal impressions; back endpaper, note n
									Persian.</p>
                        <p>Contains numerous additions and corrections in the copyist’s hand
									(e.g. f. 90r). </p>
                        <p>Includes quotations in Arabic. </p>
                        <p>Undated.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara" xml:lang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <filiation/>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
